This paper belongs to the arXiv CS sub-category of natural language processing and computational linguistics, which is covered by cs.CL. The paper discusses the use of natural language processing and text analysis to identify and extract subjective information in textual material, which is a key area of research in cs.CL. The paper also discusses techniques for comparative opinion mining, which could fall under the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), or cybernetics (cs.CY). However, given the focus on natural language processing and computational linguistics, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category.
